summary:
Experienced Legal Officer with a demonstrated history of working in international, humanitarian, criminal and human rights law. Strong legal professional skilled in Peacekeeping, Legal Writing, International Relations, Non-Governmental Organizations (NGOs), and Civil Society.
A legal expert in public international/humanitarian/criminal/human rights law; gender studies; and peace and security. A highly competent investigator/prosecutor in international criminal justice, with specialisation in the investigation and prosecution of sexual and gender-based crimes, having constituted part of the pioneer team for the Prosecutor vs Jean-Paul Akayesu, the first case to convict rape as an act of genocide and additionally headed the investigation of sexual and gender-based crimes for the Independent Commission of Inquiry on Libya. Expertise in the investigation of sexual abuse and exploitation and other forms of misconduct within the UN Common system framework.
Expert in establishing victim/witness support and protection mechanisms, with excellent communications skills, especially in relation to drafting legal documents and creating legal mechanisms/instruments enabling international organisations to fulfil their mandates
A highly experienced and successful litigator and negotiator;
An experienced UN manager and Human Resources administrator, having established and managed three UN Duty Stations from scratch;
Experienced in dispute resolution and in resolving human-resources conflicts;
Mentoring and coaching other professionals, especially women, to operate in international organisations
Empowering leader and excellent team player.
